"Split Open and Melt" by Phish (5 string bass)
From the album Lawn Boy
Transcribed by Adam Winik (ghostoffunk@yahoo.com) November, 2021

Commentary:
Melt.  I never thought I would actually attempt this, let alone finish it.  Performing in a Phish tribute band (Divided Sky out of New Jersey) has tested me 
in terms of what I can do.  As a bass player, Phish resources are extremely limited.  Brad Weiger's bass tabs on emilstabs.org are a wonderful staple, but
missing some larger tunes.  The below is a transcription of the studio version of Split Open and Melt.  Live versions vary wildly.  This was transcribed 
using the following resources:

Amazing Slow Downer app (iOS) - Hands down, the best way to learn how to play a recorded tune.  Slow down and loop sections of tracks all while keeping
pitch.

Transcription located here: https://www.accattatis.com/artists/gordon/split_open_and_melt.html
I'm not sure who to give credit to for this one, but this definitely helped with some of the faster runs.  It is not truly accurate to the record, however, 
and is missing several parts.

From start to finish, it took three weeks to learn and transcribe.  I did not focus on Mike's voicings, and I clearly tend to gravitate toward certain
strings, but I'm fairly certain the accuracy of the notes is in the mid to high 90s.  As with any tab, listen to the recording for the rhythm.

For reference, a YouTube version of me performing this is located here: https://youtu.be/quwCVRx0K6c

Any questions, feel free to email me!  Cheers!


